This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a novel boosting algorithm that combines kernel and tree boosting to improve predictive accuracy. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as boosting is a popular machine learning technique used in many AI applications. The use of regression trees and RKHS regression functions may also suggest that this paper could be categorized under the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper's focus on predictive accuracy may also indicate that it could be classified under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as accurate predictions are crucial in many computer vision tasks. Finally, the use of boosting to improve learning of functions with varying degrees of regularity may suggest that this paper could also fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
